Verena Julia Alsira MUHLBERG, Appellant, v. Luther WEEDIN, U. S. Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of Seattle, Washington Appellee. No. 7377. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 29, 1934. Anthony Savage, U. S. Atty., and Hamlet D. Dodd, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellee, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed for failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
